05932nam a22009975i 9783110219159DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20102010gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)979632627  a(OCoLC)984625912  a(OCoLC)987921494  a(OCoLC)992472371  a(OCoLC)999355178  a97831102191597 a10.1515/97831102191592doi  a(DE-B1597)36575  a(OCoLC)733240264  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aPL1547b.K87 2010 7aLAN0090002bisacsh0481ua495.17072qDE-101222/ger  aEG 93502rvk0(DE-625)rvk/23430:1 aKurpaska, Maria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aChinese Language(s) :bA Look through the Prism of The Great Dictionary of Modern Chinese Dialects /cMaria Kurpaska. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2010] 4c©2010  a1 online resource (276 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Linguistics. Studies and Monographs [TiLSM] ,x1861-4302 ;v2150 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe major aim of the book is to trace the current structuring of the Chinese language(s) on the ground of Chinese linguistics. The research presented is based on the newest and most renowned sources, namely The Great Dictionary of Modern Chinese Dialects, and the Language Atlas of China. The author discusses the role The Great Dictionary plays in analyzing the spectrum of linguistic differentiation in China and gives a detailed account of the kind of information the dictionary provides. As background, she sketches the development and current state of Chinese dialectology and dialect research. One of the author's aims is to show respect for the grand achievement the Dictionary undoubtedly is, but also to emphasize a critical distance to some of the views presented in it. Apart from being an analysis of this particular Dictionary, the book presents data about the state of modern Chinese dialectology. It provides information about different classifications of the dialects and explains on what basis the classifications are made. Looking at Chinese dialectology from a Western point of view, the author aims to understand and present the Chinese perspective. The book fills an important gap in the field of Western sinology. So far, despite lively discussions concerning the status of the varieties of Chinese and their taxonomy, full-scale studies on Chinese dialects have been almost non-existent in the Western World.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aChinese languagexDialectsvDictionaries. 0aChinese languagexPhonetics. 4aChinesisch /Sprache, Dialekte. 4aGrammatiken. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aChinese Languages.  aDialectology.  aGrammars.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2010z978311023356808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2010z9783110233605oZDB-23-DGA0 cprint